Nouziers is a commune in the Creuse department in the Limousin region in central France.
==Geography==
An area of forestry and farming comprising the village and several hamlets, situated on the border with the department of Indre, some north of Gu√©ret, at the junction of the D2 and the D56 roads with the D940.
